  "body": "## üéâ Description\r\n\r\nI'm just curious to know why this function:\r\n```\r\n  function mul(uint256 a, uint256 b) internal pure returns (uint256) {\r\n    if (a == 0) {\r\n      return 0;\r\n    }\r\n    uint256 c = a * b;\r\n    assert(c / a == b);\r\n    return c;\r\n  }\r\n```\r\nisn't written like this:\r\n```\r\n  function mul(uint256 a, uint256 b) internal pure returns (uint256) {\r\n    if (a == 0 || b == 0) {\r\n      return 0;\r\n    }\r\n    uint256 c = a * b;\r\n    assert(c / a == b);\r\n    return c;\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhy not check for b == 0 in the first if and return?\r\n\r\n- [ ] üêõ This is a bug report.\r\n- [ ] üìà This is a feature request.\r\n- [X] ?  This is a question.",
